    <h1>Sweden immigration crime statistics: what BRÅ data actually shows</h1>
    <p class="intro">Sweden's Crime Prevention Council (BRÅ) 2021 report shows that people with immigrant backgrounds are suspects at roughly 2.5 times the rate of native-born Swedes. After controlling for socioeconomic factors, the gap narrows substantially but does not disappear.</p>
    <div class="lang-switch"><a href="/faq/sweden-crime/">🌐 日本語版</a></div>
  </div>

  <section>
